cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper deals with facial expression transfer, which is a computer vision problem related to image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel adversarial training method, which is related to machine learning and could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses semantic representations to transfer facial expressions, which could be related to natural language processing and fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses datasets related to facial expressions, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of facial expression transfer in human-computer interaction, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
